UNDIAGNOSED DEATHS, OVINE - KAZAKHSTAN: (QYZYLORDA) REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
***************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 31 Jul 2015
Source: Agronews [in Russian, mach. transl., summ., edited]
http://www.agronews.ru/news/detail/141750/


Mortality of sheep has been recorded on 5 farms in the Kyzylorda [Qyzylorda] region; 1007 sheep affected, according to the head of the regional department of agriculture, Bakhyt Zhahanov. The head of the Zhanakorgan district administration decided to impose emergency measures.

"Veterinarians have collected samples for laboratory tests. At the moment, we know that the background for the losses was pasteurellosis, while the high temperatures were behind the rapid spread of he disease," said Zhahanov.

The sheep began to die a month ago, when the air temperature in the region exceeded 45 centigrade. Currently, according to Zhahanov, there is a vaccination of cattle, and sick animals are treated. More than 600 infected sheep were rescued, reports IA REGNUM.

It may be reminded that more 85 000 saiga antelopes died at the end of May 2015 in the Kostanai [Qostanay] region of Kazakhstan; the reason was considered to be an outbreak of pasteurellosis.

--
