[Zhanakorgan (map at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zhanakorgan_District#/media/File:Zhanakorgan_District_Kazakhstan.png) is a district of Kyzylorda Region in southern Kazakhstan (map at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kyzylorda_Region#/media/File:Kyzylorda_in_Kazakhstan.svg).

The above report is somewhat confusing; translation issues may contribute to the confusion. Reliable, accurate information on the event, ideally from an official animal-health authority, including clinical, epidemiological, gross-pathological and laboratory-derived information, is requested.

The mentioned recent mass mortality of saiga antelopes in Kazakhstan has been attributed by the authorities, in an OIE notification, to hemorrhagic septicemia (_Pasteurella multocida_). The exclusiveness of this bacterium as the sole causative agent of the unusual event has been debated and final confirmation requested. This is similarly applicable to the current event in sheep. According to other recent media reports, cattle and goats have apparently also been affected. This deserves confirmation or otherwise. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3551978,47245.]
